</i></p><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-14_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The Royal College of Veterinary Surgeons (RCVS) plays a pivotal role in the veterinary profession in the United Kingdom. As the regulatory body for veterinary surgeons and nurses, the RCVS ensures that education, ethics, and practice standards are upheld to protect animal health, welfare, and public health. In this blog, Dr Richard Dune delves into understanding the function and importance of the RCVS, which is crucial for veterinary professionals and organisations involved in animal care.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Previous" class="pf-slider-prev none hide"></button><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Next" class="pf-slider-next none hide"></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-30a1" data-category="Collection Suggestion" data-name="Tea" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-kYHfwS doYKjf pf-16_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hAcGzb cVhebe"><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-17_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-18_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-19_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-21_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-22_ pf-text-1">The RCVS was established in 1844 by Royal Charter.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-24_ pf-text-1">As of 2023, the UK has over 29,000 registered veterinary surgeons and more than 13,000 registered veterinary nurses.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-26_ pf-text-1">The RCVS accredits veterinary degree courses and maintains the Register of Veterinary Surgeons and Veterinary Nurses.




</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-28_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-29_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-30_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-32_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-33_ pf-text-1"><strong>The Veterinary Surgeons Act 1966</strong> - Is the primary legislation governing the practice of veterinary surgery in the UK. It defines veterinary surgery and the qualifications required to practise.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-35_ pf-text-1"><strong>Code of professional conduct</strong> - The RCVS Code of Professional Conduct sets out the ethical principles that all veterinary surgeons and veterinary nurses must follow.

</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-37_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-38_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-39_ pf-heading-1-h3">The role of the RCVS</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-41_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Regulatory functions</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-43_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The RCVS is responsible for maintaining and enhancing the quality of veterinary education and practice. This involves:



</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-45_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-46_ pf-text-1"><strong>Setting standards</strong> - The RCVS sets standards for veterinary education and professional conduct.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-48_ pf-text-1"><strong>Registration </strong>- Only appropriately qualified and registered with the RCVS can practise veterinary surgery in the UK.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-50_ pf-text-1"><strong>Fitness to practise </strong>- The RCVS investigates complaints against veterinary professionals and can take disciplinary action if necessary.


</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-52_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Educational role</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-54_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The RCVS ensures that veterinary education in the UK meets high standards. This includes:



</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-56_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-57_ pf-text-1"><strong>Accreditation </strong>- Accrediting veterinary schools and continuing professional development (CPD) programmes.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-59_ pf-text-1"><strong>Examinations</strong> - Overseeing examinations for veterinary professionals.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-61_ pf-text-1"><strong>Research and development </strong>- Supporting research and development to advance veterinary science and practice.

</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-63_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-64_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-65_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommended best practices</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-67_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Compliance with legislation</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-69_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Veterinary practices must comply with the Veterinary Surgeons Act 1966 and other relevant legislation, such as the Animal Welfare Act 2006. Best practices include:



